{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_15","type":"agent_message","text":"I have enough context to sketch the change set. I’m treating this as an additive contract layer: preserve `geometry_bundle.v1` aliases for Milestone 5 compatibility, introduce a library-owned operator bundle description and manifest block for Milestone 6, then document the design decisions in one cited note.\n\nPlan:\n1. Extend the contract module with a first-class operator bundle model:\n   - central path builder for operator archives/metadata\n   - manifest helpers for contract version, discretization metadata, and transfer discovery\n   - compatibility aliases so current geometry consumers still resolve the old paths\n2. Thread the new contract through the pipeline:\n   - update `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` and `scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` to use the centralized helpers\n   - emit per-root operator metadata into the processed manifest without breaking existing keys\n3. Add tests and docs:\n   - regression tests for deterministic serialization and operator-bundle discovery\n   - a Milestone 6 design note comparing graph vs mesh families, naming the default, fallback cases, and stability assumptions\n   - refresh pipeline notes to point downstream work at the new contract/design note."}}
